<paragraph blockId="10.[212,1172,1377,1665]" pageId="10" pageNumber="883">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mello-Leitao" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[212,463,1417,1441]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Hapalotremus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="883" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="muticus">
<emphasis box="[212,463,1417,1441]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="883">Hapalotremus muticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="2849230311" country="Brazil" county="The" location="Mello-Leitao" municipality="The" pageId="10" pageNumber="883" specimenCount="2" stateProvince="Bahia">
was described by 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03CE3B5C533FFFA6FED4FC1BFC99F922:8EB8DC91533FFFA6FD2EFA72FCE7FA03" box="[680,828,1417,1441]" country="Brazil" county="The" municipality="The" name="Mello-Leitao" pageId="10" pageNumber="883" stateProvince="Bahia">Mello-Leitão</location>
in 1923 from a single female collected in 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03CE3B5C533FFFA6FED4FC1BFC99F922:8EB8DC91533FFFA6FEE1FA52FE36FA62" box="[359,493,1449,1473]" country="Brazil" county="The" municipality="The" name="Villa Nova" pageId="10" pageNumber="883" stateProvince="Bahia">Villa Nova</location>
, state of 
<collectingRegion box="[613,682,1449,1473]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="10" pageNumber="883">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[699,766,1449,1473]" name="Brazil" pageId="10" pageNumber="883">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[789,890,1449,1473]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="7.[144,211,835,857]" captionTargetBox="[144,1104,168,803]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[144,1104,168,804]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 4. Distribution map of Hapalotremus species in South America." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4004670" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4004670/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="883">Figure 4</figureCitation>
). 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03CE3B5C533FFFA6FED4FC1BFC99F922:8EB8DC91533FFFA6FC11FA52FBF0FA63" box="[919,1067,1449,1473]" country="Brazil" county="The" municipality="The" name="Mello-Leitao" pageId="10" pageNumber="883" stateProvince="Bahia">Mello-Leitão</location>
noted a reduced number of labial cuspules (of about three or seven) and maxillary cuspules of about 10–12. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03CE3B5C533FFFA6FED4FC1BFC99F922:8EB8DC91533FFFA6FE0DFA12FE6CF9A3" box="[395,439,1513,1537]" country="Brazil" county="The" municipality="The" name="The" pageId="10" pageNumber="883" stateProvince="Bahia">The</location>
author also remarked that the tarsi of all legs are scopulated and undivided. 
<collectingMunicipality box="[339,383,1544,1568]" pageId="10" pageNumber="883">The</collectingMunicipality>
original description does not warrant recognition of the species, and, therefore the identity of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mello-Leitao" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[500,624,1577,1600]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Hapalotremus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="883" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="muticus">
<emphasis box="[500,624,1577,1600]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="883">H. muticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cannot be confirmed. 
<collectingCounty box="[893,937,1576,1600]" pageId="10" pageNumber="883">The</collectingCounty>
species is here considered 
<emphasis box="[298,497,1608,1632]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="883">species inquirenda</emphasis>
, pending the finding of the 
<typeStatus box="[809,857,1609,1633]" pageId="10" pageNumber="883">type</typeStatus>
material or availability and careful examination of material from the 
<typeStatus box="[687,735,1641,1665]" pageId="10" pageNumber="883">type</typeStatus>
locality
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
